 {"id":"bd-1nac","title":"Undo/Redo Command History Framework","description":"## Background

Text editing without undo is frustrating. FrankenTUI has:
- TextInput widget (no undo)
- TextArea widget (no undo)
- Forms (no undo)

Users expect Ctrl+Z/Ctrl+Y to work. The TimeTravel debugging feature (bd-3sa7) is for developers; users need undo.

## Solution: Command Pattern Framework

```rust
/// A command that can be undone
pub trait UndoableCommand: Send {
    /// Execute the command
    fn execute(&mut self) -> Result<(), CommandError>;

    /// Undo the command
    fn undo(&mut self) -> Result<(), CommandError>;

    /// Redo (default: re-execute)
    fn redo(&mut self) -> Result<(), CommandError> {
        self.execute()
    }

    /// Can this merge with previous command?
    /// Used for batching keystrokes into words
    fn can_merge(&self, other: &dyn UndoableCommand) -> bool {
        false
    }

    /// Merge with previous command
    fn merge(&mut self, other: Box<dyn UndoableCommand>) -> Result<(), Box<dyn UndoableCommand>> {
        Err(other)
    }

    /// Human-readable description for UI
    fn description(&self) -> &str;
}

/// Manages undo/redo history
pub struct UndoStack {
    undo_stack: Vec<Box<dyn UndoableCommand>>,
    redo_stack: Vec<Box<dyn UndoableCommand>>,
    max_history: usize,

    // Batching
    batch_mode: bool,
    current_batch: Option<CommandBatch>,
}

impl UndoStack {
    pub fn execute(&mut self, cmd: impl UndoableCommand + 'static) -> Result<(), CommandError>;
    pub fn undo(&mut self) -> Result<Option<String>, CommandError>;
    pub fn redo(&mut self) -> Result<Option<String>, CommandError>;
    pub fn can_undo(&self) -> bool;
    pub fn can_redo(&self) -> bool;
    pub fn begin_batch(&mut self, description: &str);
    pub fn end_batch(&mut self);
    pub fn clear(&mut self);
    pub fn undo_description(&self) -> Option<&str>;
    pub fn redo_description(&self) -> Option<&str>;
}

// Example: Text insertion command
pub struct InsertText {
    buffer: Rc<RefCell<String>>,
    position: usize,
    text: String,
}

impl UndoableCommand for InsertText {
    fn execute(&mut self) -> Result<(), CommandError> {
        let mut buf = self.buffer.borrow_mut();
        buf.insert_str(self.position, &self.text);
        Ok(())
    }

    fn undo(&mut self) -> Result<(), CommandError> {
        let mut buf = self.buffer.borrow_mut();
        buf.drain(self.position..self.position + self.text.len());
        Ok(())
    }

    fn can_merge(&self, other: &dyn UndoableCommand) -> bool {
        // Merge consecutive character insertions
        if let Some(other) = other.downcast_ref::<InsertText>() {
            other.position == self.position + self.text.len()
                && !self.text.ends_with(' ')
        } else {
            false
        }
    }

    fn description(&self) -> &str {
        "Insert text"
    }
}
```

## Integration

- TextInput/TextArea use UndoStack internally
- Ctrl+Z/Ctrl+Y handled automatically
- Status bar shows 'Undo: <description>'

